,Recommended,520010,34399632,Posted: 21 August,all,DATASTORM,"Climbey has produced by far the most consistently enjoyable gameplay sessions of the many VR games I have played. The climbing and jumping mechanics pioneered by this game give you a great feeling of presence and agency over your movement. The game also makes great use of the Steam workshop combined with its Built-in VR level editor.Crucially, I have found the multiplayer sessions to be surprising good, with most players willing to help out newer users with the somewhat steep learning curve. There are certainly frustrating parts to the game, but these are overshadowed by the pure satisfaction of simply overcoming them.The physics and net code are excellent, with dedicated servers delivering a level playing field and consistent play sessions for all users.I wouldn’t be put off by the early access nature of the game. As it stands there are hundreds of community levels, many of which are well made and offer interesting mechanics and challenges."
