76561198234149360,Recommended,520010,34980210,Posted: 15 September,all,xReconV2,"This game is amazing. I'm not sure why I took this long to put up a review when it's definitely one of my favorite (if not my favorite) game to play in VR. As someone who's had a pretty strong fear of heights, this game has surprisingly helped me overcome a bit of that fear and am now able to climb ladders with little anxiety. I ended up using a 360 photo of skyscrapers in Paris to add to the sensation and I believe one of the main reasons I was able to overcome some of that anxiety in real life. I still have moments where my feet and hands cramp up from levels that are open, difficult, and with very few checkpoints, but I actually enjoy these moments considering I've never felt this way outside of VR playing video games. I'd say this is a great game for seasoned VR players, but I'd extremely recommend it for those new to VR. I wish more games would adopt the climbing mechanics this game has brought to the table, but would like to see some map design and textures. The workshop features are also a great addition and probably the main reason I have so much time invested in this game. The game allows users, with creative minds, to build custom maps for the commuinity to download and play. I love it when theres a bunch of 4 or 5 star maps I haven't tried yet. They download in seconds so there's virtually no wait. This game is definitely a buy in my book and easily one I'd give 10-9.5/10."
